Czech Minister Wants to End Coal Mining Limits, Lidove Reports

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-03-01T07:03:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/czech-minister-wants-to-end-coal-mining-limits-lidove-reports.html
Czech Industry and Trade Minister
Martin Kocourek wants the government to stop using territorial
limits for managing coal mining,  Lidove Noviny  reported, citing
Kocourek.  Kocourek wants coal production to be administered by
contracts among the affected parties, including the landowners
and mining companies, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  